.TH "snd_pcm_hw_constraint_mask" 9 "snd_pcm_hw_constraint_mask" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_pcm_hw_constraint_mask \- apply the given bitmap mask constraint
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_pcm_hw_constraint_mask
.BI "(struct snd_pcm_runtime *runtime "  ","
.BI "snd_pcm_hw_param_t var "  ","
.BI "u_int32_t mask "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "runtime" 12
PCM runtime instance
.IP "var" 12
hw_params variable to apply the mask
.IP "mask" 12
the bitmap mask
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Apply the constraint of the given bitmap mask to a 32-bit mask parameter.
.SH "RETURN"
Zero if successful, or a negative error code on failure.
